   352→#### URF-002: Provider-Meta Registry
   353→**Points: 3 | Priority: Medium**
   354→
   355→**Description:** Build dynamic registry system for recruitment provider capabilities and screening attributes.
   356→
   357→**Technical Requirements:**
   358→- Automated scraping of provider API documentation
   359→- Versioned schema storage for provider attributes
   360→- Dynamic UI generation for screening criteria
   361→- Provider capability comparison and selection assistance
   362→
   363→**Acceptance Criteria:**
   364→- [ ] Provider capabilities automatically detected and stored
   365→- [ ] Screening attribute schemas updated from provider APIs
   366→- [ ] UI dynamically generates screening criteria forms
   367→- [ ] Provider comparison helps users select optimal platform
   368→- [ ] Schema versioning handles provider API changes gracefully
   369→
   370→**Provider Registry Implementation:**
   371→```typescript
   372→// @psyforge/provider-meta
   373→export interface ProviderCapabilities {
   374→  name: string;
   375→  version: string;
   376→  supportedFeatures: string[];
   377→  prescreeningAttributes: AttributeSchema[];
   378→  compensationModel: CompensationSchema;
   379→  maxParticipants: number;
   380→  geographicRestrictions: string[];
   381→}
   382→
   383→export class ProviderMetaRegistry {
   384→  private capabilities = new Map<string, ProviderCapabilities>();
   385→  
   386→  async updateProviderCapabilities(provider: string): Promise<void> {
   387→    const capabilities = await this.scrapeProviderAPI(provider);
   388→    this.capabilities.set(provider, capabilities);
   389→  }
   390→  
   391→  getCompatibleProviders(requirements: StudyRequirements): ProviderCapabilities[] {
   392→    return Array.from(this.capabilities.values())
   393→      .filter(provider => this.isCompatible(provider, requirements));
   394→  }
   395→  
   396→  private async scrapeProviderAPI(provider: string): Promise<ProviderCapabilities> {
   397→    // Provider-specific API documentation scraping
   398→    switch (provider) {
   399→      case 'prolific':
   400→        return this.scrapeProlificAPI();
   401→      default:
   402→        throw new Error(`Unknown provider: ${provider}`);
   403→    }
   404→  }
   405→}
   406→```
